data.title: The 55+ Best TÉLÉTOON Shows
data.meta_description: Over 500 TV viewers have voted on the 55+ Best TÉLÉTOON Shows. Current Top 3: Total Drama Island, 6teen, What's New, Scooby-Doo?
data.text:
Ranked By

3.3K votes

522 voters

List of popular Teletoon shows, ranked from best to worst. This list of the top current and cancelled Teletoon TV series includes the date when each show first aired, as well as which actors starred in the show. The best Teletoon TV programs of all time include the most viewed shows on Teletoon, as this list covers the entire history of the network. This list is sorted by popularity, so the shows with the most votes are at the top of the list.

List is made up of a variety of shows, including Dexter's Laboratory and Wayside.

Although television fans in different locations grew up with Teletoon on different channels, most of us got the same shows, so don't let your favorite Teletoon TV shows sink to the bottom of the list! The list of top Teletoon television shown below includes cast, creator, and premiere date when available. This list contains only TV series on the Teletoon network, even ones that are no longer on the air.

You can use this list to create a new list, re-rank it to fit your views, then publish it.

Most divisive: Sonic Underground

Over 500 Ranker voters have come together to rank this list of The 55+ Best TÉLÉTOON Shows

Sarah Gadon, Stephanie Anne Mills, Carter Hayden

Watch This Show If You Love: Camp Lazlo, My Gym Partner's a Monkey, Stoked, The Amazing World of Gumball, Adventure Time

Why Should I Stream? Total Drama Island offers a witty and humorous animated series that parodies reality television, complete with a diverse cast of characters and absurd challenges. Its sharp humor and clever social commentary on the reality TV genre have attracted a dedicated fanbase. The show's perfect combination of comedy and competition ensures viewers keep coming back for more.

Why Should I Stream? For those seeking nostalgia mixed with the chaotic triumphs and tribulations of teenage life, 6teen is an excellent choice. This animated series showcases relatable struggles faced by adolescents as they navigate everyday life while working at a shopping mall. With its blend of humor, friendship, and valuable life lessons, 6teen makes for an enjoyable watch.

Why Should I Stream? What's New, Scooby-Doo? revitalizes cherished memories or introduces new generations to Scooby-Doo and the gang - featuring modernized animation and innovative storylines combined with the classic charm of solving mysteries alongside beloved characters. The long-running franchise consistently attracts audiences across various age groups due to its timeless appeal and distinct sense of humor. Don't miss this entertaining take on a childhood favorite!

Why Should I Stream? Witness the animated phenomenon that's taken over pop culture with its relatable themes and hilarious adventures: Johnny Test. This show is a must-watch for those who appreciate comedic genius combined with a touch of sci-fi, as the series follows an 11-year-old boy navigating his chaotic life alongside two super-genius sisters and a talking dog. Don't miss out on the laughs and entertainment that made this show a beloved staple in many households around the world.

Why Should I Stream? Dexter's Laboratory is a brilliant animated series that revolves around the life of a young genius with a secret laboratory and his chaotic interactions with his sister Dee Dee. The show has garnered widespread admiration for its quirky humor, engaging character dynamics, and inventive storyline. Dexter's Laboratory stands as an essential watch for fans of animation, offering endless entertainment and laughs.

Why Should I Stream? Wayside brings to life the eccentricities of a bizarre 30-story elementary school, showcasing the zany misadventures of students and staff navigating their unconventional learning environment. With quirky characters and delightful humor, this entertaining animated series presents a light-hearted viewing experience sure to elicit chuckles from viewers across all ages.
